{"title":"First Ride Review: SRAM’s New Eagle Transmission and Stealth Brake Collection – Josh Weinberg","link":"https://theradavist.com/sram-eagle-transmission-stealth-brake-review/","date":1679407253000,"content":"<p><em>After months of <a href=\"https://www.pinkbike.com/news/srams-new-rear-mech-accidentally-leaked.html\" target=\"_blank\">leaks</a>, <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/sram-blackbox-rear-derailleur/\" target=\"_blank\">spottings</a>, and <a href=\"https://wheelbased.com/2021/04/08/rear-gearshift-mechanism-for-coaxial-installation-by-sram/\" target=\"_blank\">speculation</a>, <a href=\"https://www.sram.com/en/sram\" target=\"_blank\">SRAM</a> unveiled their newest wireless mountain groupset, <a href=\"https://www.sram.com/en/sram/mountain/collections/eagle-transmission\" target=\"_blank\">Eagle Transmission</a>, along with a collection of Stealth Brakes. This hefty product launch encompasses derailleurs, cranksets, cassettes, shift controllers, and more across XX SL Eagle, XX Eagle, and XO Eagle levels along with power meter and e-bike-specific components. SRAM also released an all-new Stealth lever body for their Level and Code brake lineup. As such there’s a lot to unpack here, which we expect to dive deeper into during the next few months of Transmission-equipped bike reviews. Today, however, let’s take a look at product highlights and some initial thoughts about these new components after a few rides on a Santa Cruz Megatower test bike that SRAM sent us a couple of weeks ago.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-12.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3072\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?w=3072&amp;quality=75 3072w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1024,512&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=2000,1000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=768,384&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1800,900&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1335,668&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=700,350&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1536,768&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918166004-GS-XXSL-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=2048,1024&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3072\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?w=3072&amp;quality=75 3072w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1024,512&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=2000,1000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=768,384&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1800,900&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1335,668&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=700,350&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=1536,768&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918167004-GS-XX-EAGLE-TRANSMN-AXS-PM-170-TTYPE-c-Side.png?resize=2048,1024&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3072\" height=\"1536\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?w=3072&amp;quality=75 3072w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=1024,512&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=2000,1000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=768,384&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=1800,900&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=1335,668&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=700,350&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=1536,768&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007918168001-GS-X0-EAGLE-TRANSMISSION-AXS-170-TTYPE-c-Side-1.png?resize=2048,1024&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.sram.com/en/sram/mountain/collections/eagle-transmission\" target=\"_blank\">SRAM Transmission</a></h3>\n<p>With SRAM’s adoption of the Universal Derailleur Hanger a few years ago, we knew something new was coming. Well, Eagle Transmission is that something. This isn’t just a few tweaks to the existing Eagle AXS, rather, it is an entirely new system with all new parts in—as SRAM describes—a rethinking of “the entire interface between frame, wheel, and drivetrain.” With no derailleur hanger or adjustment screws, the aim of this system is to allow “flawless shifting under maximum power.” That’s right: no separate hanger and no limit screws. Instead, the derailleur is attached directly to the bike frame and tensioned through a straightforward <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZQhLgsgDObN7066d5rnDhw\" target=\"_blank\">setup method as seen in this video</a> and/or with the assistance of SRAM’s new mobile app which bases tension on a number of factors including bike model, chainstay length, chainring size, etc. To maximize and optimize the capabilities of Transmission, you must outfit your bike with the complete component suite—an ecosystem, if you will—consisting of derailleur, crankset, chainring, chain, and controllers. Should you choose to use just a few parts on their own – like just adding a Transmission derailleur to your existing Eagle AXS drivetrain – SRAM claims that Transmission will not function properly for reasons described below.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission-6.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=1024,1024&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=1800,1800&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=1335,1335&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=700,700&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518160000-AM-RD-XX-SL-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v04.png?resize=2048,2048&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1024,1024&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1800,1800&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1335,1335&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=700,700&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518162000-AM-RD-X0-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=2048,2048&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1024,1024&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1800,1800&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1335,1335&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=700,700&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/007518161000-AM-RD-XX-EAGLE-AXS-T-TYPE-c-Side-v03.png?resize=2048,2048&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<h3>Derailleurs</h3>\n<p>These new XX SL, XX, and XO derailleurs are “engineered as integrated, interdependent Transmission components [where] the T-Type [Transmission Type] derailleur mounts around the wheel axle itself, contacting the cassette directly with a first-of-its-kind Hangerless Interface.” This, as SRAM point out, creates a far stronger connection as the mech mounts directly to both sides of the bike frame and the axle.</p>\n<p>All three levels feature an integrated overload clutch, which essentially decouples the motorized internals in an impact to prevent damage. There’s also a replaceable B-knuckle cover and outer link. Yes, we’re talking about a partially rebuildable derailleur. This is SRAM’s answer to those of us who may fear that Transmission eliminates the derailleur hanger’s capacity to save the derailleur by “breaking away.” Most modern thru-axle hangers are too strong to break away before the derailleur is damaged anyway, so this may be a way to give the $XXX Transmission derailleur a second or third life. We won’t know how effective it is until we bash our test derailleur hard enough to take advantage of it.</p>\n<p>Giving the derailleur such wide purchase on both sides of the dropout helps add durability, but SRAM had no way to quantify exactly <i>how</i> much. What they did have, though, is Nino Schurter. At a World Cup XCO race in August of last year, Schurter slid out in a right-hand turn, and appears to have ground the derailleur into the dirt for a good three feet. It was the sort of crash that wouldn’t necessarily rip off a derailleur, but would likely bump it out of alignment. The rest of the race appeared to be problem-free, since he ended up securing his 10th World Cup title that day.</p>\n<p>Additionally, XX SL and XX versions incorporate a two-piece lower pulley called Magic Wheel, which allows the pulley teeth to rotate independently of the pulley “spokes” if an object becomes lodged within them. Without the uncertainty introduced by a potentially misaligned derailleur hanger, Transmission cassettes and derailleurs make direct contact with each other “ensuring perfect alignment on every bike.” The derailleurs also incorporate what SRAM is calling an “Inline Cage,” where the pulley cage doesn’t just stay parallel to the cassette cogs, but instead remains continually oriented to point towards the chainring. So they could be sure they knew exactly where that chairing would be relative to the derailleur, SRAM is also introducing a dedicated Transmission crank.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/Transmission.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/006118641001-AM-FCX0-EGL-SNLPMQ174CL55DUB170BLK2G32TT-c-Side-v03.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/03/006118641001-AM-FCX0-EGL-SNLPMQ174CL55DUB170BLK2G32TT-c-Side-v03.png?w=3000&amp;quality=75 3000w, https:/